  "prompt": "Will I get refund after preparation of chart for wait listed ticket?",
  "response": "Whether you get a refund for a waitlisted ticket depends on the policies of the specific transportation service (like airlines, trains, etc.) you are using. Generally, if a waitlisted ticket does not get confirmed, you can usually expect a full refund.\n\nFor example, in the case of train bookings in India (IRCTC), if a waitlisted ticket is not confirmed by the time of the journey, you are typically entitled to a full refund. However, specific rules and procedures may vary, so it's advisable to check the terms and conditions of the booking service you used.\n\nIf you need clarification, it's best to contact their customer service or check their official website for specific refund policies related to waitlisted tickets.",
